	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'd disagree a bit on the character selection on this one.&nbsp;&nbsp;Bottom line is play what ever race you feel comfortable with.  In the long run stats don't really matter that much. You will pick up stat enhancing equipment and get your INT up to 200 without a lot of trouble.  The advantage of playing a human is that you get an Exp bonus.  As you get older and you (and everyone else) maxes out the INT at 200, you still get the exta Exp bonus. Might not see the benefit as much early on, but with INT maxed, the Exp bonus is a help and will let you level faster.  The night blind thing is a pain short term, but you get heatstone fairly quick and your summonded staffs are great light sources.  You won't be blind long (also ask a magi brother or sister to cast a heatstone or coldstone for you, never had someone say no and I do it for newbies now as well).  So the issue above with humans can be resolved short term. Don't aviod this race because of some short term issues.<br><br>In the short term stats do help out.  If you are really interested in stats then the Euridite is a great choice.  Has the highest intelligence by far (means you have to find less INT items long term).  The night blind stuff can be dealt with short term (I'm an Euridite magi and never found it to be much of an issue). Gnome is a good choice, less INT but good other stats.  The High Elf is more of a WIS type character.  Has the second lowest INT (long term won't matter, but we're talking short term here). Vision is good, but you can fix that in short order with the non infravision characters.<br><br>I would suggest taking your last 5 points and putting them into AGI or STR.  I don't see a lot of benefit in CHA.  It will help you with selling but 5 points doesn't do much.  Spend a level or two in BB and kill gnolls (or have an enchanter friend sell your stuff or get CHA items to help). It quickly raises your faction with the merchants of qeynos.  I am regarded warmly by all of them and get good prices.  The AGI will help you avoid getting hit and at lower levels that is a real benefit. The reality is 5 points really has little effect no matter where you put them. Putting them in STR lets you carry more stuff.  Again not a big benefit.  I'd stick with AGI on the last 5.<br><br>Cetus<br>The Nameless<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
